<p>ASFAA is pleased to announce and to invite you to the 3rd ASFAA Training Course, which will be held at the ASFAA Training Centre in Macao, China between 23 and 27 May, with the theme <b>Sport for All and Youth Development</b>.</p><p>Following the success of the previous two editions and with the continued support of the Macao SAR Government, the 3rd ASFAA Training Course will once again be organized by the Macao Sport Development Board. The aim is to provide a structural and practical training to personnel involved or about to engage in the field of Sport for All. It is also a valuable platform for exchange of knowledge and experience and to develop the communication network among ASFAA members, NGO and local sport for all institutions.  Successful participants will receive an official ASFAA Certificate of Completion.</p><p>Registration is now open! Please refer to the attached information for further details on registration and fees. Deadline for registration is 24 April 2015 and will be accepted on a first come, first served basis. </p><h3>For enquiries, please contact:</h3><p>Phone:</p><p>Ms. Ekie Huang <a href="tel:+853-8796 5542">+853-8796 5542</a> (Cantonese - Mandarin - English)</p><p>Mr. Helder Rosa <a href="tel:+853-8796 5615">+853-8796 5615</a> (Cantonese - English - Portuguese)</p><p>Fax:	<a href="tel:+853-8796 5611">+853-8796 5611</a> / <a href="tel:+853-2834 3708">+853-2834 3708</a></p><p>Email:	sport@macau.ctm.net </p><p></p><h3>Please download below:</h3><ul><li><a href="http://asfaa.org/pdf/Information.pdf">Course Information</a></li><li><a href="http://asfaa.org/pdf/Registration_Non Local.pdf">Registration Form for Non-Local Participants</a></li><li><a href="http://asfaa.org/pdf/Registration_Local.pdf">Registration Form for Local Participants</a></li></ul><p></p>